To make things easier, save the files in a folder called bf.
This is just a small, compact Brainfuck interpreter written in Python.

Usage:
  python pybf.py yourcode.bf

You can use it as a module as well:

import bf.pybf

sourcecode = "+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++."

bf.pybf.evaluate(sourcecode)

WARNING: The command '_' is a custom extension that deletes the '__pycache__' directory. Use it with caution.

http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brainfuck

